Date: 1/20/2026

Data stored in form of schema ( how the tables look like)
4 Types: Tables , views , stored procedures , functions

SQL: Communication tool with the database , 
-> DDL , DML , DQL , DCL , TCL 

DQL : Data Query Lang              : Retreive Data             : Select
DDL : Data Definition Lang         : Define Structure          : Create , Alter , Drop
DML : Data manipulation Lang       : Modify Data               : Insert , Update , Delete
DCL : Data Control Lang            : Contol Access             : Grant , Revoke
TCL : Transaction Control Lang     : Manage Transaction        : Commit , Rollback

Create Table company_db.test_table
(   id int
    name varchar (100)
);

select id from company_db.test_table;


Insert into company_db.test_table( id , name)
values (1, 'HK') , (2, 'PK') , (3, 'SK');

Insert into company_db.test_table( id, name)
values(5 , 'XYZ');

# Alter Table 

primary key : Referenced table , Referencing table(college)
Foreign key: (SSN is FK in college & Pk in people)

FK (person ID) , References Persons(ID)

--> On delete restrict 
--> On update cascade --> change in data in one table , then also change the data in 2nd table.


--> Not null , unique , Pk , Fk
--> Check , Default
--> Drop table , delete table , Truncate
--> Drop table: Delete data and table
--> Delete Table: Used with Where clause
--> Truncate: DML , DDL , DQL 

---> Cardinality: one to one , one-many , many to one , many to many 
CRED

--> Only one PK per entry 




 
